      <title>An Argument for Making Some Changes to PvP Resists</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12249#M12249</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I did a little research into how spell resists work PvP, and I found some interesting things.&amp;nbsp; How hard a spell is to resist doesn't seem to be based on the level of the spell, at all.&amp;nbsp; In short, I think that's wrong.&amp;nbsp; My level 70 ancient spells that required a lot of work to get should be **SMURF** tough to resist, and they need to be if I'm going to have much shot at killing melee characters simiarly leveled and geared to me.&amp;nbsp; Here's why:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I have about a 10K mana pool on my level 70 necro with nearly 1100 aa and gear that is 275-300 mana/hp per piece.&amp;nbsp; I have a level 70 War alt with gear that isn't quite as good, and not nearly as many aa (about 200).&amp;nbsp; He's 11K HP unbuffed, and 13.8 or so with typical cleric and shammy buffs.&amp;nbsp; If his resists were as high as mine (around 500) I don't think I could kill him even if he just stood there.&amp;nbsp; The reason is spell casting efficiency.&amp;nbsp; To kill him, even with just walking around buffs, I'd need to do at least 1.4 HP of damage for every 1 unit of mana that it cost me to cast a spell.&amp;nbsp; In the limited testing that I've done, I can barely muster that against my War alt even with resists of only around 300 or so.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;My most reliable spell against players is my level 70 ancient tap.&amp;nbsp; At full eficiency, it does about 2.2 HP of damage for every point of mana that it costs (1300HP for 598 mana).&amp;nbsp; Against a player at my level though, it is never going to hit for full pop.&amp;nbsp; It doesn't even hit for full pop against my War alt.&amp;nbsp; It's true that it will crit sometimes, but even the crits are for the base damage of the spell, or less.&amp;nbsp; Against my War alt, it lands for an average of&amp;nbsp;780 points of damage tested over 50 trials, and again, his resists are only around 300, so he did not resist the spell often.&amp;nbsp; That's an efficiency of 1.30.&amp;nbsp; In other words, &lt;STRONG&gt;I would be unlikely to kill him with this spell before I ran out of mana even if he just stood there &lt;/STRONG&gt;and he is not comparable to my Necro.&amp;nbsp; Throw a heal pot&amp;nbsp;into the equation, and he is literally unkillable.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Some of my other spells (especially dots) are more mana efficient than my big tap, but they are unlikely to land against a player with resists equal to mine.&amp;nbsp; Because of that,&amp;nbsp;their&amp;nbsp;practical efficiency is probably less than the tap (I'll do more testing and report the result here).&amp;nbsp; Here's why:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There are three parameters that SOE uses to determine whether a spell will be resisted PVP.&amp;nbsp; pvpresistbase, pvpresistcap, and pvpresistcalc.&amp;nbsp; These are completely independant of the resist checks that you are used to seeing.&amp;nbsp; Those only relate to whether a mob can resist the spell.&amp;nbsp; I'm not privvy to how these interact to determine whether a spell lands against a player or not, but I can tell you from testing that big negative numbers in the resist base and resistcap make a spell more likely to land.&amp;nbsp; Small negative numbers, or positive numbers probably means that the spell will land seldom, if at all, against a well geared player.&amp;nbsp; pvpresistcalc looks to be related to the level of the spell (65 and up spells seem to have a 136 calc).&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Here are the numbers for some of my best spells:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ancient Touch of Orshiak (usually lands)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistbase: -300 pvpresistcap: -400 pvpresistcalc: 136&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Fang of Death (usually&amp;nbsp;lands)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistbase: -300 pvpresistcap: -400 pvpresistcalc: 136&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Blood of Thule (sometimes land if debuff)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;pvpresistbase: -137 pvpresistcap: -194 pvpresistcalc: 136&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Chaos Venom (never lands)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistbase: -42&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistcap: -159 pvpresistcalc: 136&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Pyre of Mori (never lands)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistbase: -42&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistcap: -159 pvpresistcalc: 136&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Descecrating Darkness (never lands)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistbase: -42&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; pvpresistcap: -159 pvpresistcalc: 136&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Of these, Blood of Thule is the only dot that has much of a shot at landing, and it's a 65 spell.&amp;nbsp; As has been reported here, spells like Splurt and Pyrocuror do land, but they would not even approach the mana efficiency needed to kill a 13K + player (who will usually hit&amp;nbsp;a heal pot for&amp;nbsp;a few K more)&amp;nbsp;even with a 10K mana pool.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There is no rhyme or reason to these right now.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Sorry, but a&amp;nbsp;65 spell shouldn't be harder to resist than the 70 spell in the same line.&amp;nbsp; 70 Ancient spells that are **SMURF** hard to get because they drop from raid mobs and are no-drop should be **SMURF** hard to resist, no?&amp;nbsp; We (casters) should get better weapons for doing the hard stuff, just like the melees.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If anyone out there has a 'toon with 500ish resists and 13K or more HP&amp;nbsp;and wouldn't mind helping me do a little testing, I'd love to update this with more results to give Pinhead a some more ammo to take to SOE.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
