      <title>Re: An Argument for Making Some Changes to PvP Resists</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12266#M12266</link>
      <description>Yeah, I think that there shoud.&amp;nbsp; If it seemed like I was arguing for my&#xD;
spells only, that isn't the case.&amp;nbsp; I was just using them as an&#xD;
example.&amp;nbsp; What I was saying is that a 70 spell should be harder to&#xD;
resist than a 65 spell, regardless of what kind of spell it is, and&#xD;
that PVP resists need to be adjusted so that players at the high end&#xD;
aren't all but immune to spell based DPS.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
What SOE needs to consider is who is likely to have these spells, who&#xD;
they're likely to be fighting against PVP.&amp;nbsp; The highest level spells&#xD;
that you can get should be pretty good weapons against the highest&#xD;
level players, regardless of their class/gear, especially when cast by&#xD;
someone with high-end spell focus aas and gear.&amp;nbsp; What I was pointing&#xD;
out in this thread is that SOE can make that so if they want to without&#xD;
effecting PvE play, since the PVP resists are separate.&amp;nbsp; They have a&#xD;
pretty easy way of determining balance if they want to.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The best&#xD;
spells in the game should be capable of killing the best geared players&#xD;
in the game when cast by someone comparably geared and with a&#xD;
comparable AA level.&amp;nbsp; As I pointed out, it comes down to mana&#xD;
efficiency.&amp;nbsp; If a top player has, say, a 13K mana pool, can he kill a&#xD;
17K warrior with max resists, allowing for heal pots?&amp;nbsp; It's something&#xD;
that sony could easily test.&amp;nbsp; I think they could test right down the&#xD;
line this same way.&amp;nbsp; Someone like me with a 10K mana pool ought to be&#xD;
able to kill someone with 14K or so HP, again, with a margin to allow&#xD;
for heal pots.&amp;nbsp; An entry level 70 with a 7K mana pool should be a match&#xD;
for someone with 10-11K HP + pots, and resists that would be likely&#xD;
given their level of HP.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
If sony would just look at the typical ratio of HP to mana for players&#xD;
of roughly equal level and gear and ensure through the PVP resists that&#xD;
spells cast PVP are always efficient enough to kill a comparable&#xD;
player, they'd balance things out nicely, I think.&amp;nbsp; The only downside&#xD;
would be that it would make it pretty easy for casters to kill each&#xD;
other, since we generally have quite a bit less HP than a comparably&#xD;
geared melee class.&amp;nbsp; To overcome compensate for that, you'd probably&#xD;
have to add a whole other line of pvp resist or shielding stats to&#xD;
items that would be higher for caster equippable items than for&#xD;
comparable melee gear, which is probably more effort than SOE is&#xD;
willing to invest in it's smallish EQ PvP community.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
As for me farming 66s for PVP points, nah, not my style, and never will&#xD;
be.&amp;nbsp; I'm the type that needs an in-game reason to want to kill 'ya&#xD;
(foolish me still thinks its an RPG) and I don't have 66s contesting&#xD;
things in game with me very often.&amp;nbsp; Most of my PvP these days is with&#xD;
the zone-line campers while I'm on my way to do something else.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
Needless to say I'm not attacked by 66s camping zone-ins very often.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
